<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-605-305  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 605 305.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>InfoWorld  Nov 12 1990 v12 n46 p151(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Microsoft updates look of and adds pull-down menus tocharacter-based Word 5.5. (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Miller, Michael J.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Microsoft Corp has added a new user interface with pull-down menusand pop-up dialog boxes to its Word 5.5 word processing software.andO;The user interface is almost identical to the one used in Word forWindows and many of the obscure commands of the previous versionare renamed.andP;  Existing Word users will probably keep the oldinterface.andP;  However, the new interface will most likely appeal tonew users who run multiple applications or those who want aWindows-like interface but require the speed of a character-basedprogram.andP;  Users who do not have the hardware that Windows requireswill also find a big plus in Word 5.5.andP;  A ribbon on top of thescreen shows the font, point size and type style as well as theparagraph style.andP;  Word can also now import text or bit-mappedgraphics from the Windows clipboard.andP;  Word 5.5 is $450 andrequires 384Kbytes of free memory and at least two disk drives.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Microsoft Corp. (Product enhancement).andO;Ticker:    MSFT.andO;Product:   Microsoft Word 5.5 (Word processing software) (Productenhancement).andO;Topic:     Word Processing SoftwareEnhancementsSoftware PackagesGraphical User Interface.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>